55.2	Lorentz_transformation	Lorentz transformation	In physics, the Lorentz transformation or Lorentz-Fitzgerald transformation describes how, according to the theory of special relativity, different measurements of space and time by two observers can be converted into the measurements observed in either frame of reference.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5d/Animated_Lorentz_Transformation_frame_0031.gif
